  "root_text": {
    "sn22.159:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 22.159 ",
    "sn22.159:0.2": "15. Diṭṭhivagga ",
    "sn22.159:0.3": "Ānandasutta ",
    "sn22.159:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn22.159:1.2": "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā …pe… bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn22.159:1.3": "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena dhammaṁ desetu, yamahaṁ bhagavato dhammaṁ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti. ",
    "sn22.159:2.1": "“Taṁ kiṁ maññasi, ānanda, ",
    "sn22.159:2.2": "rūpaṁ niccaṁ vā aniccaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.3": "“Aniccaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.4": "“Yaṁ panāniccaṁ dukkhaṁ vā taṁ sukhaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.5": "“Dukkhaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.6": "“Yaṁ panāniccaṁ dukkhaṁ vipariṇāmadhammaṁ, kallaṁ nu taṁ samanupassituṁ: ",
    "sn22.159:2.7": "‘etaṁ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.8": "“No hetaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.9": "“Vedanā … ",
    "sn22.159:2.10": "saññā … ",
    "sn22.159:2.11": "saṅkhārā … ",
    "sn22.159:2.12": "viññāṇaṁ niccaṁ vā aniccaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.13": "“Aniccaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.14": "“Yaṁ panāniccaṁ dukkhaṁ vā taṁ sukhaṁ vā”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.15": "“Dukkhaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.16": "“Yaṁ panāniccaṁ dukkhaṁ vipariṇāmadhammaṁ, kallaṁ nu taṁ samanupassituṁ: ",
    "sn22.159:2.17": "‘etaṁ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? ",
    "sn22.159:2.18": "“No hetaṁ, bhante”. ",
    "sn22.159:2.19": "“Evaṁ passaṁ …pe… ",
    "sn22.159:2.20": "nāparaṁ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. ",
    "sn22.159:2.21": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "sn22.159:2.22": "Diṭṭhivaggo pañcamo. ",
    "sn22.159:3.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn22.159:3.1": "Ajjhattikaṁ etaṁmama, ",
    "sn22.159:3.2": "Soattā nocamesiyā; ",
    "sn22.159:3.3": "Micchāsakkāyattānu dve, ",
    "sn22.159:3.4": "Abhinivesā ānandenāti. ",
    "sn22.159:3.5": "Uparipaṇṇāsako samatto. ",
    "sn22.159:4.0": "Tassa uparipaṇṇāsakassa vagguddānaṁ ",
    "sn22.159:4.1": "Anto dhammakathikā vijjā, ",
    "sn22.159:4.2": "kukkuḷaṁ diṭṭhipañcamaṁ; ",
    "sn22.159:4.3": "Tatiyo paṇṇāsako vutto, ",
    "sn22.159:4.4": "nipātoti pavuccatīti. ",
    "sn22.159:4.5": "Khandhasaṁyuttaṁ samattaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn22.159:0.1": "Linked Discourses 22.159 ",
    "sn22.159:0.2": "15. Views ",
    "sn22.159:0.3": "With Ānanda ",
    "sn22.159:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn22.159:1.2": "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: ",
    "sn22.159:1.3": "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.1": "“What do you think, Ānanda? ",
    "sn22.159:2.2": "Is form permanent or impermanent?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.3": "“Impermanent, sir.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.4": "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.5": "“Suffering, sir.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.6": "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus: ",
    "sn22.159:2.7": "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.8": "“No, sir.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.9": "“Is feeling … ",
    "sn22.159:2.10": "perception … ",
    "sn22.159:2.11": "choices … ",
    "sn22.159:2.12": "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.13": "“Impermanent, sir.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.14": "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.15": "“Suffering, sir.” ",
    "sn22.159:2.16": "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus: ",
    "sn22.159:2.17": "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” ",
    "sn22.159:2.18": "“No, sir.” … ",
    "sn22.159:2.19": "“Seeing this … ",
    "sn22.159:2.20": "They understand: ‘… there is nothing further for this place.’” ",
